HEADWORD: Forward
<hw>For"ward</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE., fr. AS.
<ets>foreweard</ets>; <ets>fore</ets> before + <ets>weard</ets> a ward.
See <er>Ward</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>An agreement; a covenant; a
promise.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Tell us a tale anon, as <qex>forward</qex> is.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj></p>

